                            <comment id="13536329" author="lhofhansl" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2012 19:17:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t the source also find a new region server at the sink when one of them drops out?&lt;br/&gt;
Otherwise we could be down to one region server at sink, worst case?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13536354" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2012 19:50:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lhofhansl&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lhofhansl&quot;&gt;Lars Hofhansl&lt;/a&gt; yeah actually what is done right now is that we call chooseSinks() if we think all the RS we&apos;re talking to are dead. We could also just get a new list if one is dead, it would be a very minor change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13536375" author="lhofhansl" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2012 20:11:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I.e.:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;remove current peer if we get connection refused (means we could reach the machine, but nobody&apos;s listening, likely no need to try again)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;keep track of how many peers we removed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;after some threshold (maybe when number of a removed peers &amp;gt;= number of peers remaining, i.e. we lost 1/2 the peers), re-chose all peers from ZK then reset number of removed peers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13536377" author="lhofhansl" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2012 20:12:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oops. Didn&apos;t see you reply before I posted my last comment. I think we agree.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13536410" author="lhofhansl" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2012 20:39:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Something like this.&lt;br/&gt;
Maybe this is overkill and we should just chooseSinks again when one RS is lost.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13536427" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2012 21:13:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems overkill and chooseSinks() is cheap won&apos;t need too much new code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
